[A map of Indonesia is available at http://www.ezilon.com/maps/images/asia/political-map-of-Indonesia.gif.

The numbers of dead birds reported by the ministry are not excessive in relative terms and compared to other countries. This may be indicative of the rather small size of the affected holdings, which are, most probably, not commercial farms.

Since the start of the HPAI H5N1 event in 2003, and as of 28 Jul 2016, human cases have been reported from 16 countries with 854 cases, of which 450 reportedly died. The countries most affected are Egypt (354 cases, 117 deaths), Indonesia (199, 167), Viet Nam (127, 64), Cambodia (56, 37), and mainland China (53, 31). Its incidence in poultry, and subsequently in humans, demonstrates a seasonal pattern. The countries which have reported human cases of avian influenza A(H5N1) during the past 6 months are Egypt and mainland China.

Detailed quantitative information on HPAI H5N1 in poultry by state and month was last reported by Indonesia for the year 2014 (see at http://tinyurl.com/hyxly65, scroll down). According to the report, Indonesia applies vaccination of poultry against the disease. - Mod.AS

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4383461,184.]
